The candidate of Alliance for Democracy (AD) in the 2019 governorship election in Oyo State, Engr. Oyedele Hakeem Alao, has picked a 43-year-old Ogbomoso-born business woman, Hon. (Mrs.) Olaronke Georgina Ajibi, as his running mate. Ajibi was born on September 2, 1975. She is from Oloko’s Compound, Taara, Ogbomoso in Ogbomoso North Local Government Area of Oyo State. “Ajibi is a lover of the grassroots with strong passion for uplifting women and children in the society. Her choice was informed by the need for a government that will be more gender-friendly and recognising the importance of women in nation building which the Alliance for Democracy (AD) represents,” Alao said in a statement.  LAUTECH’s tuition hike: AD guber candidate carpets Osun, Oyo govts Oyo 2019: Political heavyweights regroup under Obasanjo’s ADC to unseat APC 2019: Ajimobi, Ladoja, Akala in fresh battle of wit